## 12. SLA SYSTEM (3-LEVEL ESCALATION)

Default: 30 min. Custom per dept saved to sla_settings.
DB CONSTRAINT: UNIQUE (department, hotel_id) — saveSLA uses onConflict: 'department,hotel_id'

fetchSLA: runs on mount AND every poll cycle — picks up manager changes without refresh
getSLALimit: slaSettings[dept] || 30 (all uses consistent)

Levels:
- Level 1 (80%): ⚠️ Orange warning to staff
- Level 2 (100%): 🚨 Red alert, task marked Violated in DB, mandatory delay reason
- Level 3 (150%): 🔴 Escalated — staff notified management alerted

handleComplete: blocks close if elapsed > limit || task.status === 'Violated'

